To securely parse an XML configuration document from an attacker-controlled `InputStream` using `DocumentBuilderFactory`, you must explicitly disable DTDs and external entity processing to prevent XML External Entity (XXE) and XML Bomb attacks.

Here is the secure implementation:

```java
import javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder;
import javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory;
import javax.xml.XMLConstants;
import org.w3c.dom.Document;
import java.io.InputStream;

public class ConfigLoader {

    /**
     * Parses an XML configuration document securely.
     *
     * @param in The input stream of the XML document.
     * @return The parsed Document object.
     * @throws Exception if parsing fails or security configurations are violated.
     */
    public static Document parseConfig(InputStream in) throws Exception {
        DocumentBuilderFactory dbf = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();

        // 1. Disable DTDs entirely to prevent XXE and XML Bomb attacks.
        // This is the primary requirement for preventing XXE in DocumentBuilderFactory.
        dbf.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);

        // 2. Explicitly disable external entities and parameter entities.
        // Even if DTDs are partially allowed, these features prevent the parser 
        // from fetching external content.
        dbf.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities", false);
        dbf.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities", false);

        // 3. Disable loading of external DTDs.
        dbf.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/nonvalidating/load-external-dtd", false);

        // 4. Set attributes to restrict access to external DTDs and schemas.
        dbf.setAttribute(XMLConstants.ACCESS_EXTERNAL_DTD, "");
        dbf.setAttribute(XMLConstants.ACCESS_EXTERNAL_SCHEMA, "");

        // 5. Enable secure processing. 
        // This helps limit entity expansion and other resource-intensive tasks 
        // to mitigate XML Bomb (billion laughs) attacks.
        dbf.setFeature(XMLConstants.FEATURE_SECURE_PROCESSING, true);

        // Create the DocumentBuilder and parse the stream.
        DocumentBuilder builder = dbf.newDocumentBuilder();

        // Note: This approach ensures the parser is configured correctly before 
        // the input stream is processed.
        return builder.parse(in);
    }
}
```

### Security Features Explained:
*   **`disallow-doctype-decl`**: Setting this to `true` instructs the parser to throw an exception if the XML contains a `DOCTYPE` declaration. This is the most effective way to block XXE.
*   **`external-general-entities` & `external-parameter-entities`**: These ensure that even if a DTD is somehow processed, the parser will not attempt to resolve external URLs or files.
*   **`FEATURE_SECURE_PROCESSING`**: This instructs the JVM to limit the amount of memory and CPU used during parsing, protecting your application against Denial of Service (DoS) attacks like the "XML Bomb."
*   **`ACCESS_EXTERNAL_DTD`/`SCHEMA`**: These are secondary barriers that restrict the parser's ability to reach out to external resources.
